{"title_page": "Texas A&M\u2013Texas Tech football rivalry", "text_new": "{{unsourced|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox sports rivalry           \n| name                  = Texas A&M\u2013Texas Tech football rivalry\n| image                 = \n| image_size            = \n| caption               = \n| team1                 = [[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M Aggies]]\n| team1logo             = Texas A&M University logo.svg\n| team2                 = [[Texas Tech Red Raiders football|Texas Tech Red Raiders]]\n| team2logo             = Texas Tech Red Raiders Logo.svg\n| sport                 = \n| firstmeeting          = October 27, 1927<br />Texas A&M 47, Texas Tech 6\n| mostrecent            = October 8, 2011<br />Texas A&M 45, Texas Tech 40\n| nextmeeting           = \n| total                 = 70\n| series                = Texas A&M leads, 37\u201332\u20131\n| largestvictory        = 1. Texas A&M, 47-6 (1927)<br>2. Texas Tech, 56-17 (2005)\n| longeststreak         = Texas A&M, 6 (1927\u201345)<br>Texas Tech, 6 (1968\u201373)\n| longestunbeatenstreak = \n| currentstreak         = Texas A&M, 3\n| currentunbeatenstreak = \n| trophy                = \n| trophy series         = \n| stadiums              =  \n}}\n{{OSM Location map         \n| nolabels = 1     \n| coord = {{coord|32.125|-98.837}}\n| zoom = 5\n| width = 295 \n| height = 250\n| caption = Locations of Texas A&M and Texas Tech\n| mark1 = Brown pog.svg\n| label1 = Texas A&M\n| mark-coord1 = {{coord|30.610278|-96.343611}}\n| label-pos1 = top\n| label-color1 = black\n| mark2 = Red pog.svg\n| label2 = Texas Tech\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|33.584|-101.878}}\n| label-pos2 = top\n| label-color2 = black\n}}\n\n\nThe '''Texas A&M\u2013Texas Tech football rivalry''' was an American [[college football]] [[college rivalry|rivalry]]{{Citation needed|date=August 2018}} between the [[Texas A&M Aggies football]] team of [[Texas A&M University]] and [[Texas Tech Red Raiders football]] team of [[Texas Tech University]]. The series began in 1927. The rivalry had continued uninterrupted since 1957 when the two schools became conference rivals.<ref>Texas Tech became a probationary member of the Southwest Conference in 1956, but did not obtain full membership and become eligible to be conference champion until 1960.</ref> Texas A&M leads the series 37\u201332\u20131. Texas A&M started the series with a 12\u20133 advantage while the two teams played each other as non-conference opponents from 1927\u20131955. Texas Tech led with a 2\u20131 record during its probationary membership in the [[Southwest Conference]] from 1957\u201359. Texas A&M led the series during the Southwest Conference years (1960\u201395) with an 18\u201317\u20131 record. Texas Tech led the series during the [[Big 12 Conference]] years (1996\u20132011) with a 10\u20136 record. In summary, Texas A&M dominated the series during the early years (1927-1955) with a 12-3 advantage, while Texas Tech leads the series in the modern era (1957-2011) with a 29-25-1 advantage. Both teams are tied with six games each for the longest winning streak. Texas Tech holds the longest uninterrupted winning streak of the series, six games between 1968 and 1973, while Texas A&M has the longest nonconsecutive winning streak, six games in 1927, 1932 and 1942 through 1945. Texas A&M currently holds a three-game winning streak but with their departure from the Big 12 Conference in 2012, it is uncertain if the rivalry will continue in the future.\n\n==Venues==\nWhen both Texas A&M and Texas Tech were members of the Southwest Conference (SWC) from 1960 to 1995, and the Big 12 Conference from 1996 to 2011, the match-up was exclusively a home-and-home series in College Station and Lubbock. In all, 29 games were played in [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock]] and 28 in [[College Station, Texas|College Station]]. Both teams held a 3-game home field advantage as the Red Raiders record was 16\u201313 in Lubbock while the Aggies record in College Station was 15\u201312\u20131.\n\nPrior to Texas Tech joining the SWC for football in 1960, 13 games of the rivalry were held at a neutral site in [[Amarillo, Texas|Amarillo]], [[Dallas]], and [[San Antonio]]. Only one game was held in Amarillo, a 7\u20130 Texas A&M victory in 1932. From 1943\u201350, the series was held at second neutral site, [[Alamo Stadium]] in [[San Antonio]]. Texas A&M held a 6\u20132 record over Texas Tech at Alamo Stadium. The 1951, 1955, 1958, and 1959 games were held at the [[Cotton Bowl (stadium)|Cotton Bowl]] in [[Dallas]] and the series at [[Fair Park]] was split 2\u20132. In the early 2000s, an effort was made to move the series back to the Cotton Bowl during the [[State Fair of Texas]] but ultimately the rivalry game remained a home-and-home series.\n\n[[File:Aggies vandalize Will Rogers and Soapsuds.png|thumb|Caption: \"Texas A&M came to Lubbock\"<br>''Riding Into the Sunset'' after being vandalized in 1969.]]\n\n==Will Rogers & Soapsuds statue==\n{{main|Riding Into the Sunset}}\nA statue of Will Rogers riding his horse, Soapsuds, sits near the main entrance to the Texas Tech campus. After originally facing West, the statue was rotated so that the rear of the horse faces towards College Station, home of rival Texas A&M Aggies.{{clear}}\n\n==Game results==\n{{Sports rivalry series table\n| format = compact | cols = 2 | series_summary = yes\n| team1 = Texas A&M\n| team1style = {{NCAA color cell|Texas A&M Aggies}}\n| team2 =  Texas Tech\n| team2style = {{NCAA color cell|Texas Tech Red Raiders}}\n\n|October 27, 1927 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |47 |Texas Tech|6\n|September 24, 1932 | Amarillo|Texas A&M |7 |Texas Tech|0\n|October 3, 1942 | College Station|Texas A&M |19 |Texas Tech|0\n|October 2, 1943 | San Antonio|Texas A&M |13 |Texas Tech|0\n|September 30, 1944 | San Antonio|Texas A&M |27 |Texas Tech|14\n|September 29, 1945 | San Antonio|Texas A&M |16 |Texas Tech|6\n|September 28, 1946 | San Antonio|Texas Tech |6 |Texas A&M|0\n|September 27, 1947 | San Antonio|Texas A&M |29 |Texas Tech|7\n|September 25, 1948 | San Antonio|Texas Tech |20 |Texas A&M|14\n|September 24, 1949 | San Antonio|Texas A&M |26 |Texas Tech|7\n|September 30, 1950 | San Antonio|Texas A&M |34 |Texas Tech|13\n|September 29, 1951 | Dallas|Texas A&M |20 |Texas Tech|7\n|October 10, 1953 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |27 |Texas Tech|14\n|September 18, 1954 | College Station|Texas Tech |41 |Texas A&M|9\n|October 6, 1955 | Dallas|Texas A&M |40 |Texas Tech|7\n|September 28, 1957 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |21 |Texas Tech|0\n|September 20, 1958 | Dallas|Texas Tech |15 |Texas A&M|14\n|September 18, 1959 | Dallas|Texas Tech |20 |Texas A&M|14\n|September 24, 1960 | College Station|Texas A&M |14 |Texas Tech|14\n|October 7, 1961 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |38 |Texas Tech|7\n|October 6, 1962 | College Station|Texas A&M |7 |Texas Tech|3\n|October 5, 1963 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |10 |Texas A&M|0\n|October 3, 1964 | College Station|Texas Tech |16 |Texas A&M|12\n|October 2, 1965 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |20 |Texas A&M|16\n|October 1, 1966 | College Station|Texas A&M |35 |Texas Tech|14\n|October 14, 1967 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |28 |Texas Tech|24\n|October 12, 1968 | College Station|Texas Tech |21 |Texas A&M|16\n|October 11, 1969 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |13 |Texas A&M|9\n|October 10, 1970 | College Station|Texas Tech |21 |Texas A&M|7\n|October 9, 1971 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |28 |Texas A&M|7\n|October 14, 1972 | College Station|Texas Tech |17 |Texas A&M|14\n|October 13, 1973 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |28 |Texas A&M|16\n|October 12, 1974 | College Station|Texas A&M |28 |Texas Tech|7\n|October 11, 1975 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |38 |Texas Tech|9\n|October 9, 1976 | College Station|Texas Tech |27 |Texas A&M|16\n|September 24, 1977 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |33 |Texas Tech|17\n|October 7, 1978 | College Station|Texas A&M |38 |Texas Tech|9\n|October 6, 1979 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |21 |Texas A&M|20\n|October 4, 1980 | College Station|Texas A&M |41 |Texas Tech|21\n|October 3, 1981 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |24 |Texas Tech|23\n|October 2, 1982 | College Station|Texas Tech |24 |Texas A&M|15\n|October 1, 1983 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |3 |Texas A&M|0\n|October 6, 1984 | College Station|Texas Tech |30 |Texas A&M|12\n|October 5, 1985 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |28 |Texas Tech|27\n|October 4, 1986 | College Station|Texas A&M |45 |Texas Tech|8\n|October 3, 1987 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |27 |Texas A&M|21\n|October 1, 1988 | College Station|Texas A&M |50 |Texas Tech|15\n|October 7, 1989 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |27 |Texas A&M|24\n|October 6, 1990 | College Station|#19 Texas A&M |28 |Texas Tech|24\n|October 5, 1991 | Lubbock|#23 Texas A&M |37 |Texas Tech|14\n|October 3, 1992 | College Station|#5 Texas A&M |19 |Texas Tech|17\n|October 2, 1993 | Lubbock|#14 Texas A&M |31 |Texas Tech|6\n|October 1, 1994 | College Station|Texas A&M |23 |Texas Tech|17\n|October 7, 1995 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |14 |#8 Texas A&M|7\n|October 26, 1996 | College Station|Texas Tech |13 |Texas A&M|10\n|October 25, 1997 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |16 |#20 Texas A&M|13\n|October 24, 1998 | College Station|#8 Texas A&M |17 |#25 Texas Tech|10\n|October 2, 1999 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |21 |#5 Texas A&M|19\n|September 30, 2000 | College Station|Texas A&M |33 |Texas Tech|15\n|November 3, 2001 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |12 |#17 Texas A&M|0\n|October 5, 2002 | College Station|Texas Tech |48 |#23 Texas A&M|47<sup>2OT</sup>\n|October 4, 2003 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |59 |Texas A&M|28\n|November 11, 2004 | College Station|#23 Texas A&M |32 |#25 Texas Tech|25<sup>OT</sup>\n|November 5, 2005 | Lubbock|#16 Texas Tech |56 |Texas A&M|17\n|September 30, 2006 | College Station|#24 Texas Tech |31 |Texas A&M|27\n|October 13, 2007 | Lubbock|Texas Tech |35 |Texas A&M|7\n|October 18, 2008 | College Station|#5 Texas Tech |43 |Texas A&M|25\n|October 24, 2009 | Lubbock|Texas A&M |52 |#24 Texas Tech|30\n|October 30, 2010 | College Station|Texas A&M |45 |Texas Tech|27\n|October 8, 2011 | Lubbock|#24 Texas A&M |45 |Texas Tech|40\n}}\n\n== See also == \n* [[List of NCAA college football rivalry games]]\n\n==References==\n{{